#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &atomic-update;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: update_split_brain.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "taroth 2014-11-19: not sure this is still valid, see bsc#905330"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &atomic-update; is based on tools that manage two copies of the system "
"and allow easy recovery after an update failure. The delivered tools require "
"a special disk partition setup. Every copy of the system resides on a "
"primary partition of its own. If an update fails, you can always switch back "
"to the previous state of the system, which is available on the other "
"partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strict Partitioning Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The implementation has strict requirements on disk partitioning: the first "
"root partition is <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> and must not occupy more "
"than half of the entire disk size. Then the tools will create <filename>/dev/"
"sda2</filename> for the system's second root partition. Further partitions "
"if available are shared on both root partitions&mdash;take their size into "
"account, and reduce the size of the first partition accordingly; this is a "
"rough calculation:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The size of the complete disk minus size of <systemitem>sda1</systemitem> "
"minus <systemitem>sda2</systemitem> is the free space of additional "
"partitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the system with <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> as the single root "
"partition and with less than half of the entire disk size."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Customize the installed system as needed. Make sure to have the "
"<systemitem>multi-update-tools</systemitem> package installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <command>multi-update-setup --partition</command>, which creates the "
"system's second root partition (<filename>/dev/sda2</filename>) of the "
"similar size."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Partition the rest of the disk as needed and continue with customizations(*)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <command>multi-update-setup --clone</command> to copy the system to the "
"other partition. With this command you also change the <filename>/</"
"filename> (root) entry in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> of the target "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "If needed, do further customizations(*)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <command>multi-update-setup --bootloader</command> to initialize the "
"boot loader setup. The boot loader menu will then contain an entry to boot "
"the other system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "&grub; Boot Loader Mandatory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Installation of the &grub; boot loader is mandatory. The tools are not "
"compatible with other boot loaders."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there are no customizations to be done as marked with (*), run "
"<command>multi-update-setup --complete</command> which performs all the "
"three steps."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updating the Other System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <command>multi-update</command>. This command runs <command>zypper</"
"command> in a <systemitem>chroot</systemitem> environment and updates the "
"other system&mdash; it does not matter which one is active. Its boot menu "
"will be offered as the default at boot time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the updated system has a damaged boot loader after the update, you must "
"change the <quote>Active</quote> flag and set it for the root partition of "
"the other system to boot it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the updated system does not boot, you need access to the boot loader menu "
"to select the other system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "For more information about &grub;, see <xref linkend=\"cha.grub2\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: update_split_brain.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Limitation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: update_split_brain.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The root partition must be mounted by partition name, by ID, or in another "
"way. Mounting by partition UUID or by label is not supported."
msgstr ""

